---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import FloridaTreeCareAdvisor from "../../components/FloridaTreeCareAdvisor.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Florida Tree Care Advisor"
  description="Use ProTreeTrim's Florida Tree Care Advisor to get practical tree care guidance by Florida region, season, and homeowner concern."
>
  <header class="tool-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-kicker">Florida Homeowner Tool</div>
      <h1>Florida Tree Care Advisor</h1>
      <p>
        Get practical, Florida-specific tree care guidance based on your area, season,
        and the issue you are seeing on your property.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container tool-main">
    <section class="intro-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>Use this before comparing tree service options.</h2>
        <p>
          Florida tree care changes by region. A live oak in North Florida, a palm in South Florida,
          a stump near a pool deck, and a storm-damaged pine on a rural lot all create different
          questions for homeowners. This tool helps you organize the first steps before requesting
          a quote or reading a deeper guide.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside>
        <strong>Not a diagnosis.</strong>
        This tool is general guidance only. For cracked, leaning, uprooted, or storm-damaged trees,
        keep people away from the hazard area and contact a qualified local provider.
      </aside>
    </section>

    <FloridaTreeCareAdvisor />

    <section class="after-tool-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>What this advisor is best for</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Understanding whether a tree issue is routine, worth monitoring, or more urgent.</li>
          <li>Finding relevant ProTreeTrim guides for storm prep, palms, roots, stumps, and permits.</li>
          <li>Preparing better photos and questions before speaking with a tree service company.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>When to call instead</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>A tree is blocking a driveway, road, sidewalk, or building access.</li>
          <li>A cracked, leaning, or uprooted tree threatens a roof, fence, pool cage, or structure.</li>
          <li>Large limbs are hanging, splitting, or resting on a structure after a storm.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .tool-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f2f24 0%, #1b4332 70%, #245b43 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 5.5rem 1.5rem 4.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 5px solid #ea580c;
  }

  .tool-kicker {
    color: #ffb703;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .tool-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 8vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1.02;
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .tool-hero p {
    color: #bbf7d0;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 1.2rem auto 0;
  }

  .tool-main {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 12rem;
  }

  .intro-grid,
  .after-tool-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(280px, 0.8fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .intro-grid h2,
  .after-tool-grid h2 {
    color: #123d2b;
    font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .intro-grid p,
  .after-tool-grid li {
    color: #475569;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .intro-grid aside {
    background: #fff7ed;
    color: #9a3412;
    border: 1px solid #fed7aa;
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .intro-grid aside strong {
    display: block;
    color: #7c2d12;
    font-weight: 900;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .after-tool-grid {
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }

  .after-tool-grid > div {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 1.6rem;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04);
  }

  .after-tool-grid ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .intro-grid,
    .after-tool-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
